## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [fc2-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;fc2-1 seedlings do not become green when grown in short days (4 or 8 hours light).They are defective in de-etiolation response in short days. This is likely due to accumulation of protoporphyrin IX which in turn causes production of reactive oxygen species and triggers chloroplast degradation pathway.
   - [fc2-1/pub4-6]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Seedlings green normally when exposed to 4 hour light cycle. Plants still produce ROS and chloroplasts look abnormal but do not degrade.
